### Clinic Management System - API Testing File
### Use with VS Code REST Client Extension
### https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=humao.rest-client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@contentType = application/json

###
### AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINTS
###

### 1. Register New Patient
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}

###
### 2. Verify Email (use token from register response)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "token": "PASTE_VERIFICATION_TOKEN_HERE"
}

###
### 3. Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###
### 4. Alternative Login (for testing)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "admin@test.com",
  "password": "admin123"
}

###
### USER MANAGEMENT ENDPOINTS (ADMIN ONLY)
###
### Authorization: Bearer {JWT_TOKEN}
###

### 5. Get All Users (need JWT token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

###
### 6. Create New Doctor User (Admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Dr. Sarah Smith",
  "email": "sarah@clinic.com",
  "password": "docPassword123",
  "phone": "+9876543210",
  "role": "doctor"
}

###
### 7. Create New Receptionist User (Admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Rebecca Johnson",
  "email": "rebecca@clinic.com",
  "password": "recPassword123",
  "phone": "+8765432109",
  "role": "reception"
}

###
### 8. Create New Admin User (Admin)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Admin User",
  "email": "newadmin@clinic.com",
  "password": "adminPass123",
  "phone": "+7654321098",
  "role": "admin"
}

###
### 9. Get User by ID (Admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/PASTE_USER_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

###
### 10. Get User by Email (Admin)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/email/john@example.com
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

###
### 11. Update User (Admin)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/PASTE_USER_ID_HERE
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

{
  "name": "Updated Name",
  "phone": "+1111111111"
}

###
### 12. Delete User (Admin)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/PASTE_USER_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

###
### TEST SCENARIOS
###

### Scenario 1: Complete Registration Flow
### Step 1 - Register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Test Patient",
  "email": "testpatient@example.com",
  "password": "testPass123",
  "phone": "+1234567890"
}

###
### Scenario 1 - Step 2 - Verify Email (copy token from Step 1 response)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-email
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "token": "COPY_TOKEN_FROM_STEP_1"
}

###
### Scenario 1 - Step 3 - Login with verified email
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "testpatient@example.com",
  "password": "testPass123"
}

###
### Scenario 2: Admin User Management
### Prerequisites: Be logged in as admin, copy JWT token

### Step 1 - List all users
GET {{baseUrl}}/users
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN

###
### Step 2 - Create new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "name": "Dr. Test Doctor",
  "email": "testdoctor@clinic.com",
  "password": "docTestPass123",
  "role": "doctor"
}

###
### Step 3 - Update the user (use ID from Step 2 response)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/USER_ID_FROM_STEP_2
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "name": "Dr. Test Doctor Updated",
  "phone": "+5555555555"
}

###
### Step 4 - Get updated user
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/USER_ID_FROM_STEP_2
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN

###
### Step 5 - Delete the user
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/USER_ID_FROM_STEP_2
Authorization: Bearer ADMIN_JWT_TOKEN

